      "t": "Mobileye CEO Amnon Shashua to step aside as company pushes into robotaxis, robotics",
      "d": "Shashua has been invited to take the chairman of the board seat.",
      "u": "https://techcrunch.com/2026/07/23/mobileye-ceo-amnon-shashua-to-step-aside-as-company-pushes-into-robotaxis-robotics/",
      "m": "07. 23. PM 10:40",
      "ts": 1784846408000,
      "fullText": "In Brief Posted: 3:40 PM PDT · July 23, 2026 Image Credits: Bridget Bennett / Bloomberg / Getty Images Kirsten Korosec Mobileye CEO Amnon Shashua to step aside as company pushes into robotaxis, robotics Mobileye founder and CEO Amnon Shashua plans to step down from the top leadership post after nearly three decades, just as the company pushes into robotaxis and humanoid robots. Shashua will remain CEO until Mobileye hires a replacement, according to a regulatory filing Thursday. Mobileye got its start making computer vision chips based on Shashua&#8217;s academic research at Hebrew University in Israel, and grew into a major supplier of the chips that power automotive safety and driver-assistance features. It had the largest IPO in Israel&#8217;s history, was acquired in 2017 by Intel for $15.3 billion, then spun back out as a publicly traded company in 2022, though Intel remains its largest shareholder. Under Shashua, Mobileye also moved beyond selling chips to automakers and began building its own systems that handle autonomous driving , which it now supplies to Volkswagen and its MOIA subsidiary. In January, the company acquired Shashua&#8217;s humanoid robotics startup Mentee Robotics for $900 million , which Shashua called part of &#8220;Mobileye 3.0,&#8221; the next phase of the business focused on robotics and automotive AI. Mobileye also said in June it would expand beyond its supplier status to launch its own robotaxi service in a U.S. city in 2027. Topics In Brief , Mobileye , Transportation October 13 &#8211; 15 San Francisco Scale faster. Grow your portfolio. Gain practical expertise. No matter your goal, Disrupt can empower you. Save up to $330 toda y! REGISTER NOW Newsletters See More Subscribe for the industry’s biggest tech news TechCrunch Daily News Every weekday and Sunday, you can get the best of TechCrunch’s coverage. TechCrunch Mobility TechCrunch Mobility is your destination for transportation news and insight. Startups Weekly Startups are the ",
